subSubSection.paragraph:
Head.
Frons and vertex brownish-yellow, labrum yellow and rarely reddish-brown (10% of specimens examined), labial and maxillary palpi brown. Antenna slender, yellow, apical antennomere darker (
Fig. 169
), length of second to third antennomere 0.62–0.70 (mean: 0.65), and length of third to fourth antennomere 0.55–0.62 (mean: 0.58) (
Fig. 171
). Eyes large with long interocular distance (
Fig. 169
), and width of eye to interocular distance 0.50–0.57 (mean: 0.53).
